   HTMLCountry2

                    COMMITTEE ON THE RIGHTS OF THE CHILD

    Group photo of current Members of the Committee on the Rights of the
                        Child © Danielle Kirby/OHCHR

Membership

   The Committee on the Rights of the Child is composed of 18 independent
   experts who are persons of high moral character and recognized
   competence in the field of human rights.

   Members are elected for a term of four years by States parties in
   accordance with article 43 of the Convention on the Rights of the
   Child. Members serve in their personal capacity and may be re-elected
   if nominated.

   Also available:
     * Information on former CRC members from 1991 to 2013
     * Information on former CRC members from 2005 to 2013

   The membership of the Committee on the Rights of the Child as of
   2017is:

                               Name of Member

                           Country of Nationality

   Ms. Suzanne AHO ASSOUMA*"

   Togo

   Ms. Amal Salman ALDOSERI *
   (Vice Chairperson)

   Bahrain

   Ms. Hynd AYOUBI IDRISSI**

   Morocco

   Mr. Bragi GUDBRANDSSON**

   Iceland

   Mr. Philip JAFFE**

   Switzerland

   Ms. Olga a. KHAZOVA*

   Russian Federation

   Mr. Cephas LUMINA*

   Zambia

   Mr. Gehad MADI**
   (Vice Chairperson)

   Egypt

   Faith MARSHALL-HARRIS**

   Barbados

   Mr. Benyam Dawit MEZMUR *

   Ethiopia

   Mr. Clarence NELSON**

